observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:

create an Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality, and submit the corresponding report therefrom in strict compliance to Section 206 of Volume I of the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs and COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020; 

direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the ledger cards for each item of the PPE after the inventory taking;

through the Municipal Accounting Office, undertake continuous reconciliation on the result of the physical count with the property and accounting records and adjust the book of accounts and the property records, as warranted, to reflect the correct balances of the affected PPE accounts in order to fairly present the PPE accounts in the financial statements as of year-end; and

instruct the concerned offices to study the applicability of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 which provides the guidelines and procedures in the conduct of physical count of PPE, recognition of PPE Items found at station and disposition for non-existing/missing PPE items, for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances of government agencies to facilitate fair presentation of PPE accounts in the financial statements.

