The Municipal Treasurer orient and require the custodian of the accountable forms, to issue the same in strict numerical sequence;

The collectors prepare Reports of Accountability for Accountable Forms (RAAF) at least once a month for submission to the Municipal Treasurer for the preparation of the consolidated RAAF. The monthly CRAAF prepared by the Municipal Treasurer accompanied by the individual RAAFs of the collectors shall be submitted to the Audit Team in the ensuing month; and



The Management devise specific control measures in the issuance of cash tickets, such as assigning serial numbers, tearing off of cash tickets to avoid possible re-issuance and conduct of surprise inspection by the authorized personnel, to ensure proper control and accounting thereof.

4.9. Based on the foregoing, we recommended that:
The Municipal Treasurer frequently conduct a surprise audit in the cash tickets to identify any collections that remains unremitted to her;
All collectors turn over their collections daily and intact to the Liquidating Officer, accompanied by their corresponding Report of Collections and Deposits;
The Liquidating Officer verify the daily Report of Collections and Deposits and reconcile the balances contained therein with actual balances on hand; and
The Liquidating Officer turn over intact daily the cash collections and the accompanying RCD to the Local Treasurer.
